CSSStyleProperties.summary: The CSSStyleProperties interface of the CSS Object Model (CSSOM) represents inline or computed styles available on an element, or the styles associated with a CSS style rule.

CSSStylePropertiesCssFloat.summary: The cssFloat property of the interface returns the CSS {{cssxref("float")}} property.

remarks.para: This is the result of invoking on the object with float as an argument.

When setting, it invokes with float as the first argument, and the given value as the second argument.
The given value must be a valid value for the float property.

CSSStylePropertiesCssFloat.value: A string.When set to the null value, that null value is converted to the empty string (""), so csd.cssFloat = null is equivalent to csd.cssFloat = "".
